      <section eId="sec_CCRP-729-1">
        <num>CCRP 729.1</num>
        <heading>729.1. Â Court's disposition of motion for discovery; vacation or restriction of order</heading>
        <subsection eId="CCRP-729-1__subsec_A">
          <num>A.</num>
          <content>
            <p>A motion for discovery shall not be denied without a contradictory hearing unless it appears on the face of the motion that, as a matter of law, the moving party is not entitled to the relief sought.</p>
          </content>
        </subsection>
        <subsection eId="CCRP-729-1__subsec_B">
          <num>B.</num>
          <content>
            <p>Upon a sufficient showing by either party, the court may at any time vacate, restrict or defer an order for discovery, or make such other order as is appropriate.
Added by</p>
          </content>
        </subsection>
        <authorialNote marker="source">
          <p>Source: https://www.legis.la.gov/legis/Law.aspx?d=112737</p>
        </authorialNote>
      </section>
